# ClaudeHut memory index — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

This is the **committed, always-loaded index**. It names what is stored where so the agent reads the
on-demand files only when needed. Keep it concise (≤ ~150 lines).

## Always loaded (via @import in CLAUDE.md)
- `PROJECT.md` — stack, build tool + verify command, layers, entry points, test strategy.
- `LANGUAGE.md` — vocabulary lock (canonical term → meaning).

## On demand (read when relevant — NOT @import-ed)
- `architecture.md` — package/layer map, dependency direction. Read when exploring structure.
- `reuse-index.json` — catalog of reusable components (services, utils, configs). Read during the brainstorm reuse-scan.
- `learnings.jsonl` — cross-session learnings. Top-N injected at SessionStart; full file read on demand.

## Path-scoped rules (auto-load when touching matching files)
- `.claude/rules/*.md` — controller, service, persistence, reactive, messaging, testing, security,
  plus always-on `project-structure.md` and `vocabulary.md`.

## Dispatch convention (always applies)
When dispatching multiple independent subagents (Review's auditors; Brainstorm's explorer + reuse-scanner;
disjoint `[P]` implement tasks), issue all the Agent tool calls in one message — independent calls in the
same message run concurrently. Use qualified agent types (`claudehut:claudehut-<name>`).

